title: Short Sellers Are Giving Up Amid COVID Bull Market: Bloomberg
text: It's not just Tesla Inc (NASDAQ: TSLA) skeptics who have been hit hard this year, as Benzinga noted yesterday. Short sellers in general have had such a terrible go of it that many have given up.

title: Economic Preview: Raging pandemic singes U.S. economy and signals darker days ahead
text: Where there's smoke, there's fire, the saying goes. The record surge of coronavirus cases is generating plenty of smoke --- and darkening the outlook for the U.S. economy.

title: Stocks still have major upside potential with the Fed poised to backstop sluggish stimulus progress, says the world's largest wealth manager
text: The Senate Majority Leader's rejection of Democrats' stimulus proposal and a rare divergence between the Federal Reserve and the US Treasury has investors on edge as uncertainties rise. But despite the back-and-forth, "the case for further upside in global equities remains intact," Mark Haefele, chief investment officer at UBS Wealth Management, which oversees $1.4 trillion in assets, said in a note on Friday.
